<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Dr Carrie Dunn</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Dr </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Carrie Dunn</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> [WAS0001]</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Profile</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Sociologist: PhD in social science</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">L</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ecturer in information and communications at Manchester Metropolitan University</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">About this </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">paper</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">This briefing paper argues that women and girls need to feel that sport is open to them as spectators and participants – both equally important - rather than seeing it as a male-dominated field, which is still the case. I highlight some of the key a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">spects of female sports fandom, and suggest that despite the growing numbers of women involved in sport, it is still institutionally sexist, creating problems for those who object to covert and overt sexism.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The paper </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">focuses on my completed research proj</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ect into </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the experience of female fans of men's professional football in England, and based on a questionnaire completed by 100 respondents of varying demographic followed by 27 in-depth interviews. I also interviewed club directors and representatives of </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the FA and Football League to add context to my findings.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">I am currently working on a research project looking at the significance of elite sporting role models to young participants, focusing on football and cricket.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Summary findings</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">My key findings ar</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">e as follows:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">female</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> football fans tend to be </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">created in childhood</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> through the influence of significant individuals, primarily the father. I suggest this also applies to other 'male-dominated' sports; respondents also reported fandom of sports including c</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ricket and rugby.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">whether</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> or not a respondent had siblings (male or female) was not particularly significant; the family </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">setting an example</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> to the female fan in childhood, encouraging her to believe that sport was open to her, shaped the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">rest of her sporti</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ng career as a fan and as a participant</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">younger</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> female football fans (under 20) also see themselves as </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">e</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ntitled to play the game</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> as of right. Older generations of female fans reported occasionally playing as children, but not as teenagers or older. This m</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ay link to the FA taking over control of the game for women in 1993.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">female</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> football fans continue to recognise </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">sexism in the game</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, whether overt and explicit or covert and implicit; this ranges from lack of women's toilet facilities to media coverage.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">female</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> football fans are more likely to become </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">involved in the cooperative supporters' trust movement</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, possibly because of its democratic structures meaning their contributions are recognised.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; orphans:0; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the football authorities and clubs themselves have historically</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> had </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">very little data on women involved in football</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, whether as participants or spectators, and remain reluctant to act on issues relating to sexism, distancing themselves from accusations of 'political correctness'.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; page-break-before:always; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Key points</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">1)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The role of the family</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">F</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">emale fans tend to be introduced to football by family members, who encourage their spectatorship, often as part of a familial tradition. This mostly occurs in childhood. I suggest that if girls are put off football or they are told that it is “for boys”, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">they accept and do not question this, and remain outside football for the rest of their lives. Occasionally women begin watching football in adulthood, but my findings indicate that this is not particularly common, giving the lie to the stereotype that adu</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">lt women go to football only to keep their husband or boyfriend company.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Respondents indicated that strong personal influences played a large role in initiating them into football support, with a particular individual (a family member, a friend or colleag</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ue) being identified as a significant initiator in 91% of questionnaire respondents; only 9% of respondents claimed they first went to football alone and of their own volition.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The father was named as the key influence by half of respondents, and I sugges</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">t that this reflects a more involved (and possibly more egalitarian) style of parenting in the late 20</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and early 21</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> century, where fathers can spend leisure time with their daughters, not just their sons, through a shared regular football support.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:200%; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Table 1: Person prompting respondents into attending matches</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0pt; width:478pt"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:203.3pt"><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:200%; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Person responsible</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:t